vanilla porridge with coconut sugar caramelised bananas + a little bee pollen for brunch!
-
for the caramelised bananas... add a tsp coconut oil or butter into a fry pan with a couple of tbs coconut sugar. stir to combine & melt the coconut oil. cut two bananas in half lengthways & add to the pan cut side down. cook for a few mins until caramelised. serve warm over porridge or pancakes or even ice cream. delish!
-
have a lovely day all! ash x #gatherandfeast

spelt chocolate fondants 🙌🏻🍫 just in case you haven't seen enough chocolate over the last couple of weeks 😬! a great way to use up any excess chocolate you might have lying around from Easter... also if you are gluten intolerant, simply swap the spelt flour for buckwheat flour!✌🏻️recipe on the G&F site (link in bio). enjoy friends! x #gatherandfeast

black grape, plum + banana smoothie! using the most delicious seedless black grapes from @sunworldgrapesaustralia… so good! simply blend 1 frozen banana, 1/2 cup frozen grapes, 1 frozen plum blended with almond milk + vanilla. enjoy!✌🏻x #gatherandfeast #sunworldgrapes #sponsored #seedlessgrapes
